<div class="subject-container">

  <div class="subject-header">
    <h1>Control Systems</h1>
    <p>
      Control Systems regulate the behavior of machines
      to achieve desired output automatically.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      Control systems ensure accuracy, stability, and efficiency
      in automated machines and industrial processes.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Core Concepts</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="info-card">
        <h3>Open Loop</h3>
        <p>No feedback mechanism.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <h3>Closed Loop</h3>
        <p>Uses feedback for accuracy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <h3>Stability</h3>
        <p>System response over time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <h3>PID Controller</h3>
        <p>Widely used industrial controller.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Applications</h2>
    <div class="highlight">
      Used in robotics, automation, aerospace,
      industrial machines, and vehicles.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Exam Tips</h2>
    <p>
      ✔ Practice block diagram reduction  
      <br>
      ✔ Understand stability criteria  
      <br>
      ✔ Solve numerical problems  
    </p>
  </div>

</div>